  "prompt": "What is it like to attend dental school?",
  "response": "Attending dental school is a challenging and comprehensive educational experience. Here are some key aspects:\n\n1. Academic Rigors\n- Intense science-based curriculum\n- Heavy course load in anatomy, physiology, biochemistry\n- Extensive study of dental techniques and procedures\n- Demanding academic schedule\n\n2. Clinical Training\n- First two years focus on classroom and lab work\n- Later years involve hands-on patient treatment\n- Practice procedures on mannequins before treating actual patients\n- Learn various dental specialties like orthodontics, oral surgery\n\n3. Time Commitment\n- Long days, typically 8am-5pm\n- Additional evening and weekend study time\n- Requires significant personal dedication\n- Challenging work-life balance\n\n4. Financial Investment\n- Expensive tuition\n- Significant student loan debt\n- Cost of dental equipment and supplies\n- Potential opportunity cost of delayed income\n\n5. Personal Skills Development\n- Develop precise manual dexterity\n- Learn patient communication\n- Develop professional demeanor\n- Manage stress and high-pressure environments\n\n6. Physical Demands\n- Standing for long periods\n- Precise hand movements\n- Potential physical strain\n\nOverall, dental school is challenging but rewarding, preparing students for a professional healthcare career.",
